sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    actor U as User
    participant F as Frontend
    participant A as Auth Service
    participant D as User Database
    participant C as Cache
    participant M as MongoDB Audit
    participant K as Kafka
    participant G as Google Authenticator App

    Note over U,K: 1. User registers account
    U->>F: Fill register form
    F->>A: POST /auth/register {fullName, email, password}
    A->>D: Check user by email
    D-->>A: User exists / not found

    alt Email already exists
        A->>M: Log REGISTER FAILED {email, reason: EMAIL_ALREADY_EXISTS}
        A-->>F: 409 Email already exists
        F-->>U: Show register error
    else Email available
        A->>A: Hash password
        A->>A: Assign role (admin if in ADMIN_EMAILS, else user)
        A->>D: Create user {id, fullName, email, passwordHash, role}
        D-->>A: User created
        A->>M: Log REGISTER SUCCESS {userId, email, role}
        A->>K: Publish user.registered event
        A-->>F: 201 {id, fullName, email, role, isTwoFactorEnabled}
        F-->>U: Show account created
    end

    Note over U,C: 2. User starts 2FA setup
    U->>F: Open 2FA setup
    F->>A: POST /auth/2fa/init {userId}
    A->>D: Find user by id
    D-->>A: User found
    A->>A: Generate TOTP secret
    A->>A: Generate QR / manual key
    A->>A: Generate setupToken
    A->>C: Save temporary secret (key: auth:2fa:setup:{userId}:{setupToken}, TTL: 300s)
    C-->>A: Temporary secret stored
    A->>M: Log ENABLE_2FA_INIT INFO {userId, setupToken}
    A-->>F: 200 {qrCodeDataUrl, manualEntryKey, setupToken}
    F-->>U: Display QR code / manual key

    Note over U,G: 3. User adds account in Google Authenticator
    U->>G: Scan QR code or enter manual key
    G-->>U: Generate 6-digit code

    Note over U,D: 4. User confirms 2FA setup
    U->>F: Enter 6-digit code
    F->>A: POST /auth/2fa/confirm {userId, code, setupToken}
    A->>D: Find user by id
    D-->>A: User found
    A->>C: Get temporary secret by setupToken
    C-->>A: Secret found / not found

    alt Setup session expired
        A-->>F: 400 Setup session expired or not found
        F-->>U: Show expired session message
    else Secret found
        A->>A: Verify code with temporary secret

        alt Code is valid
            A->>D: Save permanent 2FA secret
            A->>D: Update isTwoFactorEnabled = true
            D-->>A: 2FA enabled
            A->>C: Delete temporary secret
            C-->>A: Temporary secret removed
            A->>M: Log ENABLE_2FA_CONFIRM SUCCESS {userId}
            A->>K: Publish user.two_factor_enabled event
            A-->>F: 200 Two-factor authentication enabled successfully
            F-->>U: Show success message
        else Code is invalid
            A-->>F: 401 Invalid 2FA code
            F-->>U: Show invalid code message
        end
    end

    Note over U,K: 5. User login (without 2FA)
    U->>F: Fill login form
    F->>A: POST /auth/login {email, password}
    A->>D: Find user by email
    D-->>A: User found / not found

    alt Invalid credentials
        A-->>F: 401 Invalid credentials
        F-->>U: Show login error
    else Valid credentials - 2FA disabled
        A->>A: Generate accessToken (15m) + refreshToken (7d)
        A->>M: Log LOGIN SUCCESS {userId, email, role, viaTwoFactor: false}
        A->>K: Publish user.logged_in event
        A-->>F: 200 {status: SUCCESS, accessToken, refreshToken}
        F-->>U: Show dashboard
    else Valid credentials - 2FA enabled
        A->>A: Generate challengeId
        A->>C: Save challenge (key: auth:login:challenge:{challengeId}, TTL: 300s)
        C-->>A: Challenge stored
        A-->>F: 202 {status: REQUIRE_2FA, challengeId, userId, email}
        F-->>U: Show 2FA code input
    end

    Note over U,G: 6. User gets 2FA code from Google Authenticator
    U->>G: Open app
    G-->>U: Generate 6-digit code

    Note over U,K: 7. User verifies 2FA login
    U->>F: Enter 6-digit code
    F->>A: POST /auth/login/2fa {email, challengeId, code}
    A->>C: Get challenge by challengeId
    C-->>A: Challenge found / not found

    alt Challenge expired
        A-->>F: 400 Login challenge expired or not found
        F-->>U: Show expired challenge message
    else Challenge found
        A->>D: Find user by email
        D-->>A: User found
        A->>A: Verify 2FA code with permanent secret

        alt Code is valid
            A->>A: Generate accessToken (15m) + refreshToken (7d)
            A->>C: Delete challenge
            C-->>A: Challenge removed
            A->>M: Log VERIFY_LOGIN_2FA SUCCESS {userId, email, role, challengeId}
            A->>K: Publish user.logged_in event
            A-->>F: 200 {accessToken, refreshToken}
            F-->>U: Show dashboard
        else Code is invalid
            A-->>F: 401 Invalid 2FA code
            F-->>U: Show invalid code message
        end
    end

    Note over U,A: 8. User refreshes access token
    U->>F: accessToken expired
    F->>A: POST /auth/refresh {refreshToken}
    A->>A: Verify refreshToken signature
    A->>D: Find user by id

    alt Invalid or expired refreshToken
        A-->>F: 401 Invalid or expired refresh token
        F-->>U: Redirect to login
    else Valid refreshToken
        A->>A: Generate new accessToken (15m)
        A->>M: Log REFRESH_TOKEN SUCCESS {userId, email, role}
        A-->>F: 200 {accessToken}
        F-->>U: Continue session
    end

    Note over U,M: 9. Admin monitors audit logs
    U->>F: Open admin dashboard
    F->>A: GET /admin/audit-logs?page=1&limit=20 {Authorization: Bearer accessToken}
    A->>A: Verify accessToken + check role === admin

    alt Not authenticated
        A-->>F: 401 Missing or invalid authorization header
        F-->>U: Redirect to login
    else Authenticated but not admin
        A-->>F: 403 Admin access required
        F-->>U: Show forbidden error
    else Admin authenticated
        A->>M: Query audit logs with filters
        M-->>A: Paginated audit logs
        A-->>F: 200 {items, total, page, limit}
        F-->>U: Display audit logs table
    end

    Note over U,C: 10. Admin debugs Redis cache
    U->>F: Open debug tools
    F->>A: GET /admin/debug/redis/health {Authorization: Bearer accessToken}
    A->>C: Ping Redis
    C-->>A: Pong
    A-->>F: 200 {status: ok, connected: true}
    F-->>U: Show Redis status

    F->>A: GET /admin/debug/login-challenge/{challengeId} {Authorization: Bearer accessToken}
    A->>C: Check key exists + get TTL
    C-->>A: exists + ttlSeconds
    A-->>F: 200 {type, key, exists, ttlSeconds}
    F-->>U: Show challenge debug info

    F->>A: GET /admin/debug/2fa-setup/{userId}/{setupToken} {Authorization: Bearer accessToken}
    A->>C: Check key exists + get TTL
    C-->>A: exists + ttlSeconds
    A-->>F: 200 {type, key, exists, ttlSeconds}
    F-->>U: Show 2FA setup debug info